{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d0065319-8f8f-4145-9adf-b0493f8e0948","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` but is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_zSfVZWZ00GnUVFtcFQZZSW","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-bf723318d9ba40149451d317e15d1164/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-bf723318d9ba40149451d317e15d1164/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"0f630dc7-1138-4133-b4e1-5077096a2949","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear earlier in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` (listed first) — depends on `Domain.fs` (`open BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` (listed second)\n3. `Program.fs` (listed third) — depends on both\n\nThe problem is that `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` uses types from `Domain.fs`. In F#, a file can only use definitions from files listed above it in the project file.\n\n\nThe fix is straightforward: reorder the files so `Domain.fs` comes first since it has no dependencies, then `Services.fs` which depends on it, and finally `Program.fs` which depends on both.","outputTokens":478,"requestId":"1910:B9052:130FE2A:156BC86:6A066E94"},"id":"ffb5cb93-dd33-440a-9d82-b846550ec623","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:53:48.446Z","parentId":"5b92b1a7-6810-4235-8879-ee4a56868552"}
